Up in flames: A Chinese woman accidentally set fire to £20,000 meant for her husband's construction workers

Hao Bin stashed the money inside her stove, but forgot it was there and set fire to it while making tea

Mrs Bin, 35, was inconsolable after the blaze, but her husband Wang, 39, said he had forgiven her

She only realised her grave error when she went to add some more wood and saw the plastic bag filled with Chinese bank notes was almost entirely incinerated.

Mrs Bin, from Shaoshan in central China's Hunan province, threw water onto what was left of the cash, but it was too late.

The devastated woman took the charred remains to the Bank of China, but officials told her that, as less than half of each note was left, they could not exchange them for new money.

Mr Bin, 39, who owns a small construction company and needed to pay his workers a total of £20,000, said he had forgiven his wife. 

