Mr Bin said the fire was a 'hard blow' but that he would be able to cope, despite losing £20,000 cash

He said: 'We had not been paid ourselves yet for our work, but I needed to pay the workers so we borrowed the money from friends and family, and we wanted somewhere to keep it safe for a day before paying it out.

'It was a hard blow, and my wife is devastated. But I have forgiven her, and we will survive.' 

Many Chinese people choose to hide money at home because of a lack of trust in banks, with some hiding them in pillowcases and socks to keep them safe from thieves.

